    <body>
      <div xml:id="NA350-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">itu talaimakaḷ ūṭal maṟuttāḷ colliyatu.</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">This is what SHE said, being one who refuses [him while] quarrelling.</p>
        </div>
      <div xml:id="NA350">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            veṇṇe larinar taṇṇumai verīip</l>
<l>            paḻaṉap palpuḷ ḷiriyak kaḻaṉi</l>
<l>            vāṅkuciṉai marutat tūṅkutuṇa rutirun</l>
<l>            tērvaṇ virāa ṉiruppai yaṉṉaveṉ</l>
<l>            ṟolkaviṉ ṟolaiyiṉun tolaika cāra</l>
<l>            viṭēeṉ viṭukkuve ṉāyiṟ kaṭaiik</l>
<l>            kavavukkai tāṅku matukaiyaṅ kuvavumulai</l>
<l>            cāṭiya cāntiṉai vāṭiya kōtaiyai</l>
<l>            yākil kalaṅkaḻīi yaṟṟum</l>
<l>            vāral vāḻi kavaiiniṉ ṟōḷē.</l>
            </lg>
        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>            Even if my old beauty is lost,</l>
<l rend="indent">            like Iruppai of generous Virāṉ [who has many?] chariots,</l>
<l rend="indent2">            where the trailing clusters on the Marutam trees with bowing branches</l>
<l rend="indent2">            drop off by the fields, when many birds retreat to the pond,</l>
<l rend="indent3">            frightened by the Taṇṇumai drum of the cutters of white paddy,</l>
<l rend="indent4">            let it be lost.</l>
<l>        I will not let [you] come near.</l>
<l rend="indent3">            If I let you,</l>
<l>        you have a garland that is faded, you have sandal-paste spoiled(?)</l>
<l rend="indent">            by strong plump breasts that endure [your] hands in copulation, urgently(?).</l>
<l>        It [is] like<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">aṟṟu</term> certainly functions here as a kind of comparison particle, perhaps in the position of a predicate noun. But what of the -<term xml:lang="ta">um</term>?</note> removing an unfit pot.</l>
<l>        Don’t come, live, with your shoulders having embraced [someone else].</l>
<lg type="alternate" sameAs="10b">
    <l>Don’t come, may she live who stands embraced [by you].<note place="foot">Thus the second possibility of splitting the <term xml:lang="ta">sandhi</term>, <term xml:lang="ta">kavaii niṉṟōḷē</term>. Slightly dubious here is the function of nil. Do we have to understand it as an auxiliary conveying the notion of permanence?</note></l>
</lg>
        </lg>
      </div>
    </body>
